column5: Well another fine day perch fishing off Port Maitland ...talked to fishlips quick on the cell  to see if the bite was on and it was  thanks Jamze ;D...headed out 3,2 miles from the pier to 65 fow and it was none stop for all these boys till we ran outa minnows ...sure can go through alote of minnows with 7 people fishing ...still some good weather left get out and enjoy ....
Good job guys! Enjoy the feed.
Wow, nice Erie Jumbos. Soon enough I will be into the perch!! Fall is the best time to get um'
Ah, you're killin me Steve. That is what I was planning to do on Saturday, but......well you know, you saw. *sigh*
